<div><h3>SCSV 2340 - Introduction to Social/Human Service Organizations </h3>  <hr>Designed for those engaged in or planning to work in Social Services agencies. Course topics include: getting to know the service organization, the distinguishing features of organizations, supervision, the work environment, practice in host settings, work conditions, sources of and coping with change, and improving agency quality. By using a combination of case studies, experiential, and didactic approaches, students are encouraged to enhance their sense of empowerment regarding these complex issues.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> varies<br><br></div>		</td>
